TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bessler, Wolfgang
AU  - Blake, David
AU  - Lückoff, Peter
AU  - Tonks, Ian
T1  - Fund Flows, Manager Changes, and Performance Persistence*
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfx017
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 22
IS  - 5
SP  - 1911
EP  - 1947
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Most empirical studies suggest that mutual funds do not persistently outperform an appropriate benchmark in the long run. We analyze this lack of persistence in terms of two equilibrating mechanisms: fund flows and manager changes. Using data on actively managed US equity mutual funds, we find that if neither mechanism is operating, winner funds (top-decile ranked in previous year) continue to significantly outperform loser funds (bottom-decile ranked in previous year) by 4.08 percentage points per annum. However, the difference between previous winner and loser funds declines to zero within one year if the two mechanisms are acting together. Thus, equity mutual fund out- and underperformance are unlikely to persist in well-functioning financial markets.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfx017
ER  - 



